revisions.rev:
{{Use British English|date=July 2011}} This is a list of verified [[People of United Kingdom|British]] [[supercentenarian]]s (people from the [[United Kingdom]] who have attained the age of at least 110 years). There have been 118 verified supercentenarians from the United Kingdom.<ref name="GRG">[http://www.grg.org/Adams/E.HTM GRG Validated Living Supercentenarians] The Gerontology Research Group (GRG) lists persons as living whose age has been validated and confirmed to be alive within the past year. Retrieved 11 May 2011.</ref><ref name="Supercentenarians who lived in the United Kingdom">[http://www.grg.org/Adams/L/UK.HTM GRG Verified Supercentenarian Cases - United Kingdom (As of 16 April 2007)] Retrieved 11 May 2011.</ref> The oldest person ever from the United Kingdom was [[Charlotte Hughes (supercentenarian)|Charlotte Hughes]], who died in 1993 aged 115 years 228 days. As of {{date}}, there are 8 [[list of living supercentenarians|verified living supercentenarians]], 2 pending, and 1 unverified in the United Kingdom, the oldest of whom is [[Violet Wood]] age {{age in years and days|1899|9|2}}.
==Living British supercentenarians== Below is a list of the oldest living people from the United Kingdom. The reported age of those listed as 'verified' has been validated by an international body that specifically deals in [[longevity]] research. The reported age of those listed as 'pending' is backed by at least one supporting document, but not the three necessary for validation. The reported age of those listed as 'unverified' is not backed by any of the documents necessary for validation by such an institution.
